% Automatisch generiert — Thema: Marijuana Legalization
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro74).  % [pro] A 2012 study found that smoking a joint a day for seven years was not associated with adverse effects on pulmonary function.
arg(pro62).  % [pro] Legalized recreational marijuana already exists in several US states.
arg(pro62b).  % [pro] In Colorado and Washington, voters passed ballot initiatives to legalize recreational marijuana.
arg(pro2).  % [pro] For instance, in Colorado, analysts recommend that taxing the drug could raise millions of dollars each year.
arg(pro27).  % [pro] Loosening marijuana laws would help many people affected by current marijuana prohibition.
arg(pro27b).  % [pro] Repealing marijuana prohibition would help all people affected by current marijuana prohibition.
arg(pro60).  % [pro] Supporters of the status quo say the new industry has helped revitalize an area that has long struggled economically.
arg(con105).  % [con] The commercials' underlying message was essentially correct.
arg(con106).  % [con] Research even suggests that marijuana use might be linked to a higher risk of prescription drug use.
arg(con36).  % [con] Authorities should think twice about legalizing marijuana.
arg(con84).  % [con] The humorous stories about pot users having a horrible memory are not an urban legend that is simply put forward by everyone, from Hollywood films to treatment centers for addiction.
arg(con104).  % [con] Research also shows a link between marijuana use and a motivational syndrome characterized by reduced determination and drive.
arg(con21).  % [con] Anyone who has experienced marijuana addiction knows that the addiction is profound.
arg(con21b).  % [con] Some people can remain functional for many years while addicted to marijuana before experiencing difficulties.
arg(con21c).  % [con] When the high from marijuana wears off, people increase their consumption to regain the high, which leads them into difficulties.

% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(con106, pro74).  % [undermining] conf=70 — B cites research linking marijuana use to higher prescription‑drug use, challenging the safety implication of A.
